<P><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">
<IFRAME FRAMEBORDER=1 ALIGN=CENTER width=100% HEIGHT=200 SCROLLING=YES SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/Forum21/HTML/002359.html">
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#000050"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#FFFFFF" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Caper</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">This is really more a question for a FAQ. If any higher-level warrior would like to do one, I'd be happy to contribute all the ignorant questions I can think of  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/smile.gif"><P>This is a poll.  What do warriors do with their practice points?<P>I spent 20 on fletching before starting the long climb to mastery in that skill, and I regret it.  Early fletching components cost mere coppers.<P>I spent 20 on Bind Wounds but am still uncertain about that.  At 6 silver a pop, bandages are a little too expensive for me to use often, and I don't have any mage friends to summon them for me.  I'd rather wait 5 or 10 minutes and get to full health the long way.  (That tells you how low level I am.)<P>I just got the Bloodforge Hammer and have been trying to get my 2H skill up because it's my only magic weapon, but with a delay of 50 that's not going to be fast.  In a couple hours soloing my 2H blunt marched all the way up to (5).  I'm a Gnome, so I'm pretty brainy, but yee gads, that's slow.  And here I've got 20 some odd points sitting with my guild master.<P>So I'm wondering if there's something I should be saving these practice points for?  Am I going to be kicking myself at level 35 because I wasted a bunch of practice points on 2H blunt?<P>Caper the Insanely Strong Gemchopper<BR>12 Warrior on Vallon Zek<BR>Master Smith<BR>&lt;Peacemaker&gt; guild leader</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Darodar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Nope, no need to kick yourself.  I haven't checked lately, but I probably have 60 or so practice points gathering dust right now.  You got pretty good use out of yours.  Trade skills are about all you can use them for that will do you any good.  Yeah, it only cost coppers, but you saved a bunch by giving yourself a head start.  When I first started, I put most of mine into sense heading, which was stupid.  Basically, you get all the training points you will ever need by second level.  Put 1 into kick, 1 into bash, 1 into taunt, and save 4 for parry, ripost, dodge, and disarm.  the other 3 you can do with as you please.  But seriously, bind wounds is a good one...I find it hard to gain any skill in it.  I will start to bind, and be full health before I've done it once because the cleric healed me.  But it is very useful at lower levels when you actually do solo.<P><BR>As for the 2H blunt, get yourself a fine steel great staff and use it whenever you can.  It has a delay of 36, which will give you more skill checks, and should raise your skill up more quickly.  I use FS daggers to raise piercing skill because they are so fast.  Once I have the skill maxxed, I move to the better weapons.<P>Hope this helps<P><B>Darodar Steelstorm<BR>43 Warrior<BR><I>Society of Shadows - Prexus</I></B><BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Ruatha</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica"><I>So I'm wondering if there's something I should be saving these practice points for? Am I going to be kicking myself at level 35 because I wasted a bunch of practice points on 2H blunt?</I><P>Highly doubtful.  Heck, half the time I forget about them entirely.  As Darodar said, you only <I><B>need</B></I> a few points, namely enough to learn the following skills:<P>Taunt<BR>Bash<BR>Dodge<BR>Dual Wield<BR>Double Attack<BR>Parry<BR>Riposte<BR>Disarm<P>These are all the skills which require the investment of one point to activate.  So that's 8 points.<P>How you spend the rest is entirely up to you.  Personally, I put 10 into Dual Wield and 10 into Double attack.  I think I put 15 into Riposte.  The rest I spent on trade skills and learning languages.<BR><P>------------------<BR>Ruatha Kneeslasher &lt;Wings of Honor&gt;<BR>39th Level Gnome Warriorette</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Warduh</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">U tell me what do to do with my skill points i have all my points except for the one i used to train everything i think i have 155 Training points lol <P>------------------<BR>WARDUH<BR>OGRE WARROIR<BR>ME SMASH ME BASH <BR>ME KILL ALL</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">treestout</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I haven't used any training points since 30.  So, chances are, unless you're learning a trade skill, you'll have a high surplus in your higher levels.  Hmm.. maybe i'll become a tailor when i retire.<P>------------------<BR>"First you cleave the knee, then you cleave the head."<P>Meyer Anklebane,<BR>on taking down Hill Giants<BR>45 Halfling Warrior, Xegony<P>"I am NOT a smurf!  There are no smurfs in Everquest!"</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Naroon</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I first started playing a druid.  I played back when the game first started and in 2 betas before the official release date.  <P>Well, I leveled past my friends and restarted a warrior.  I had alot of good armour and such, so my friends proceeded to help me level up to their levels.  So I did a ton of combat. <I>(I am a warrior after all...=) </I><P>But the one thing I skipped in my youth was swimming lessons at the local YMCA.  At Level 30, I had a whole 17 points in Swimming.  I guess that is a problem when you leveled by your friends in order to play with your friends.<P>So I recently sunk 60 skill points into swimming.  An obscure skill that is often overlooked but VERY usefull.<P>------------------<BR><I>My Karma has run over your Dogma.</I></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Keryath</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I dumped mine into 2hd Blunt also. Just such a pain to get up.<P>BUT NO LONGER!<P>Head down to Lake rathe from SK. Hook a left and look for orcs. In the middle tent, grab that shovel!<P>only 4 dam, but the delay is in the low 20s, and it's FREE! Get a chanter friend to speed you and go play whack a mole (or puppy, if you're in sol b)  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/biggrin.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Taivlan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">This is what you use all those prcatice points for.<P>Learn all the languages in the game! hehe.<P>I am currently excellent at Dwarvish, Gnome, Elvish, good at halfling, ogre, erudite,and know a little of dark elf, elder tier'dal/kobold, barbarian, lizardman, goblin, gnoll, combine speech, and some others I'm probably forgetting.    <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/wink.gif"><P>------------------<BR>Kaldolaf Stormhammer<BR>22nd level Stormguard<P>[This message has been edited by Taivlan (edited February 08, 2000).]<p>[This message has been edited by Taivlan (edited February 08, 2000).]</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
